cs.LO, cs.CC, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new notion of computability and discusses its relation to intuitionistic logic and constructive mathematics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper shows that viable strategies are Turing complete, which is a result in computational complexity theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the implementation of high-level computational processes and their symbolic representations. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as game semantics is a technique used in the study of programming languages and has applications in AI. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the generalization of some well-known theorems in computability theory.
